sub_title: Environmental Planner|Nature-lover|Passionate about developing society w/o changing the ecosystem with the use of data
summary:
As an environmental planner, throughout my career I have always been passionate about developing society, and finding new ways to do so, without changing the ecosystem and without damaging nature. Nowadays I am really interested how we can go beyond this with the use of data and data science. 

In Eritrea, I worked in a mining exploration company in the GIS and data management team, creating geological maps to discover the potential of new mining areas. 

I have been living in the Netherlands for 4 years now. I now work at the Municipality of The Hague (work experience program – werkervaringsplek), as part of the GIS team. I am mapping roads, houses, actually all activity in the city. My ambition is to become a GIS specialist. Besides public sector organizations, also interested to work at commercial organizations and development projects internationally.  

My areas of expertise include: specialist in environmental planning, GIS and Data Management. I am an introvert with good collaboration skills within my own team and with other colleagues. I work with focus, in a very precise manner with excellent time management skills. 

If you would like to learn more about me and how I can be an added value to your organization and workforce, please contact me via Inmail. Always happy to meet in person too!
